---
description: Mandatory updates to AI_LEDGER, BACKLOG, MEMORY, PROMPT_LOG, README, and related docs
alwaysApply: true
---

# Project recording (mandatory)

Record work in repo files so humans and future sessions can audit AI activity.

## Every user message

- **Automatic:** `.cursor/hooks/log-user-prompt.sh` appends to `PROMPT_LOG.md` (timestamp + full prompt).
- **Agent backup:** If the hook did not run, append the user's exact prompt to `PROMPT_LOG.md` before other work.

## After each completed coding task

Append one row block to `AI_LEDGER.md`:

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| **Prompt/Intent** | User request (verbatim or tight paraphrase) |
| **Tool** | Cursor Agent |
| **Output Summary** | What was delivered |
| **Files Modified** | Paths touched |
| **Commit** | Conventional Commit message if committed; else `—` |

## Significant decisions

Append to `MEMORY.md`: *What was decided / Why / What was rejected*.

## Failed approaches (2+ attempts)

Append to `ERRORS.md`: *What didn't work / What worked / Note for next time*.

## Backlog

When an issue is done, mark `[x]` in `BACKLOG.md` with the matching GitHub issue id.

## README and architecture docs

- **README.md:** Update only when setup, quick start, branch strategy, or doc index changes.
- **ARCHITECTURE.md / DECISIONS.md:** Update when design or ADRs change.

## Session end

When the user says `session end` or `let's stop here`, append to `MEMORY.md`: *Worked on / Completed / In progress / Decisions / Next priorities*.

## Do not

- Skip `PROMPT_LOG.md` for any user message.
- Commit or mark backlog done without human approval when `claude.md` review gate applies.
